summary:
Transcranial direct current stimulation (tDCS) has not been studied or validated for differentiating unresponsive wakefulness syndrome from minimally conscious states; existing literature focuses solely on therapeutic applications of related techniques like TMS, without supporting diagnostic utility. Standard tools such as EEG, SSEP, and behavioral assessments remain established for accurate differentiation. 

